This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks related to fashion landmark detection, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel approach for enforcing structural layout relationships among landmarks using multiple stacked layout-graph reasoning layers, which involves reasoning over structural graph nodes to achieve global layout coherency. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), as well as multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR) due to the visual nature of the fashion landmark detection task.
